Entry Hall~
The immensity of the Compass Tower's entry hall overwhelms you.  The
beige stones of the walls seem lit from an unknown source, leaving the high
ceiling in relative darkness.  In the center of the chamber lies a wide
monument, bearing a sword and shield.  On the facing edge of the monument is
a small silver plaque.  Tall marble archways provide access to vast
corridors running to the west and east, and oaken double doors mark the exit
to the south.  To the north, behind the pedestal is a small alcove.  
~
